{
  "texts": [
    "However, despite these efforts, fraudsters continue to invent new techniques to circumvent these security measures as well as avoid detection, making it a constant battle [20], [21].Today, machine learning models have also been successfully trained to recognize fraud patterns effectively.",
    "These they learn through features classification either from the normal behavior cum signature in transactions or the quick detection of unusual activity in the transaction pattern indicative of a fraudulent profile.",
    "A variety of such machine learning (ML) models that have been successfully used or implemented include Logistic Regression [22]- [24], Deep Learning [25]- [27], Bayesian model [28], Naive Bayes [29], Support Vector Machine [30], [31], K-Nearest Neighbors [32], Random Forest [33], [34], and other models [35], [36] that have been effectively used to detect credit card fraud.",
    "Many of these have drawbacks with their flexibility in feature selection, importance, and accuracy.",
    "Our study adopts a Random Forest (RF) with synthetic minority oversampling feature selection techniques used on the Kaggle dataset."
  ]
}